Next, with $h_n = \\tau_p(n)$, we used equation (D1) to compute  the sequence $\\overline\{j_\{\\tau_p\}\}$. We then ``deformed''\
it by prepending $c$ to $\\overline\{j_\{\\tau_p\}\}$. We denote this deformation as $\\overline\{j^\{(c)\}_\{\\tau_p\}\}$.\
Then, once more applying equation (D1), we compute a sequence $\\overline\{h^\{(c)\}_\{\\tau_p\}\}$ from $\\overline\{j^\{(c)\}_\{\\tau_p\}\}$. We formed the list of pairs \
$(c, n! h^\{(c)\}(n))$. (These are just the values of the determinants from Lemma 2.2 in this situation; but it is a situation in which we can bypass calculating the determinants and, by that expedient, achieve significant time savings.) \
