\\subsubsection*\{Column E: Galois Representation Surjective for All Primes?\}\
For a prime $\\ell$, this is the Galois representation\
$$\\rho_\{E,\\ell\}: \\text\{Gal\}(\\overline\{\\mathbb\{Q\}\}/\\mathbb\{Q\}) \\to \\text\{GL\}_2(\\mathbb\{Z\}/\\ell\\mathbb\{Z\})$$\
arising from the action of the absolute Galois group on the $\\ell$-torsion $E[\\ell]$. The answer is ``N'' (False) if there exists at least one prime $\\ell$ for which $\\rho_\{E,\\ell\}$ is not surjective.\
