\\subsection*\{ Potential issues\}\
\
\\begin\{enumerate\}\
\\item Rank computation: For curves of large rank ($\\geq 2$), \\texttt\{E.rank()\} may be slow or fail. The BSD conjecture is used heuristically for rank 0 and 1. All curves in this dataset ($N \\leq 54$) have rank $\\leq 1$, so all rank computations are provably correct.\
\
\\item Generator computation: For rank 1 curves, \\texttt\{E.gens()\} returns provably correct generators using Cremona's algorithm. Heights are computed to machine precision ($\\approx 10^\{-15\}$ relative error).\
\
\\item Galois representations: The method \\texttt\{non\\_surjective()\} is provably correct for the primes it returns, but could theoretically miss exceptional primes beyond SageMath's computational limits. For $N \\leq 54$, all computations are complete.\
\
\\end\{enumerate\}\
